headline: Nasdaq falls, copper hits new high, CarMax upgrade: Market Minute
summary: Here are some of the stories Wall Street is watching on Wednesday, March 26. The tech-heavy Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC) is trading lower midday, being dragged down, in part, by declines in Nvidia (NVDA) and Tesla (TSLA). Copper (HG=F) prices hit a new high on concerns President Trump may put a tariff on copper imports. CarMax (KMX) shares are trading slightly higher after being upgraded to Overweight at Stephens. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Stephens upgrades CarMax to Overweight ahead of its Q4 results
summary: Investing.com -- Stephens upgraded CarMax Inc (NYSE:KMX) to Overweight from Equal-Weight and raised its price target to $90 from $86 ahead of the company’s fiscal fourth-quarter 2025 results. The company is expected to report earnings on April 10.

headline: Wingstop, CarMax, health stocks: Analyst calls
summary: There are a few stocks on the move thanks to analyst calls. Wingstop (WING) was initiated with an Overweight rating at Wells Fargo. headline: CarMax Stock Gets Upgraded Before Earnings. The Shares Jump.
summary: Investors should buy  CarMax  stock ahead of earnings, Stephens said in an upgrade of the shares.  Analyst Jeff Lick boosted his rating on shares of CarMax, a seller of used vehicles, to Overweight from Equal Weight on Wednesday.  The stock popped 1.7% to $75.50 Wednesday morning.
